This paper is about learning deep neural networks, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields in computer science. However, given that the paper focuses on the generative model view of deep nets, it is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the structure of neural networks with random edge weights, which could also make it relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions the use of features in the learning algorithm, which could relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
